    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Cultures of several Latin peoples from what is now Romania, Moldova, and the southern Balkan Peninsula, south and west of the Danube River; the term was used by Germanic people to distinguish the Roman descendants from the indigenous people in this area.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
